obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12503)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12503&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Betwa River Board Act, 1976.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, after consultation with the`
  line `Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 25th October, 1976, vide notification No. G.S.R. 1518(E), dated 14th October, 1976, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(i)`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12504)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of control by the Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12504&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is expedient`
  line `in the public interest that the Central Government should take under its control the regulation and`
  line `development of the inter-State Betwa River and River Valley to the extent hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12505)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1993, s. 2, for "Rajghat Reservoir" (w.e.f. 27-8-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12505&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Betwa River Board established under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) "Executive Committee" means the Executive Committee constituted under section 5;`
  line
  line `(d) "member" means a member of the Board and includes the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under section 22;`
  line
  line `(f) "Rajghat Dam" means the Dam described in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(g) ^1["Rani Laxmibai Sagar"] means the reservoir created by the construction of the Rajghat`
  line Dam;
  line
  line `(h) "regulations" means regulations made by the Board under section 23;`
  line
  line `(i) "rules" means rules made by the Central Government under section 22.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12506)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment and incorporation of the Betwa River Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1977, s. 2, for clauses (a) and (b) (w.e.f. 26-12-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12506&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be`
  line `established for the purposes of this Act, a Board to be called the Betwa River Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, and to contract and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Union Minister in charge of Irrigation shall be the Chairman of the Board and the other`
  line `members of the Board shall be the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) where the same Union Minister is not in charge of both Irrigation and Power, the Union`
  line `Minister in charge of Power or such Minister or Deputy Minister in the Union Ministry or`
  line `Department in charge of Power as may be specified in this behalf by the Union Minister in charge of`
  line Power;
  line
  line `(b) the Chief Ministers of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh; and`
  line
  line `(c) the Ministers of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh in charge of Finance, Irrigation and`
  line `Power:]`
  line
  line `Provided that when a proclamation made under article 356 of the Constitution is in force in relation to`
  line `the State of Madhya Pradesh or Uttar Pradesh, the Central Government may appoint three persons to`
  line `represent such State on the Board and the persons so appointed shall vacate their offices upon the`
  line `revocation or cesser of operation of such proclamation.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may permit any officer of the Central Government or the Government of Madhya`
  line `Pradesh or Uttar Pradesh to attend any of its meetings and take part in the proceedings but such officer`
  line `shall not be entitled to vote.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board may associate with itself, in such manner and for such purposes as may be determined`
  line `by regulations, any person whose assistance or advice it may desire in complying with any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act and a person so associated shall have the right to take part in the discussions of the`
  line `Board relevant to the purpose for which he has been associated, but shall not be entitled to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12507)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12507&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `constitute an Executive Committee consisting of officers of that Government and officers of the`
  line `Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(2) The composition of the Executive Committee shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) an officer of the Central Government shall be the Chairman of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) the Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh shall have equal representation.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the general superintendence and control of the Board, the management of the affairs of`
  line `the Board shall vest in the Executive Committee and the Chairman and other members of the Committee`
  line `shall assist the Board in such manner as the Board may require.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the rules, and to the directions of the Board, the Executive Committee may exercise any`
  line `power and do any act or thing which may be exercised or done by the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The procedure to be followed by the Executive Committee and all other matters relating to the`
  line `Executive Committee shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12508)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of the Board or the Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12508&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line No
  line `act or proceeding of the Board or the Executive Committee shall be invalidated by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in the Board or the Executive Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the composition of, or in any appointment to, the Board or the Executive`
  line Committee;
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Board or the Executive Committee not affecting the`
  line `merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12509)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Chief Engineer and Financial Adviser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 1977, s. 3 (w.e.f. 26-12-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12509&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after consultation`
  line `with the Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh, appoint an Engineer (to be the Chief`
  line `Engineer of the Board and to be known as the Chief Engineer, Rajghat Dam Project), and a Financial`
  line `Adviser, and a Secretary, to the Board from amongst the officers of the Governments of Madhya Pradesh`
  line `and Uttar Pradesh:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall, so far as practicable, ensure that officers from the same`
  line `State do not hold the posts of Chief Engineer and Secretary at the same time:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that the Central Government may, with the concurrence of the Governments of`
  line `Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh, appoint an officer of the Central Government as the Financial`
  line Adviser.]
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the general superintendence and control of the Board and the Executive Committee, the`
  line `Chief Engineer of the Board appointed under sub-section (1) shall be the Chief Executive Officer of the`
  line `Board and shall exercise and discharge--`
  line
  line `(a) such powers and duties as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to him by the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) such other powers and duties as may be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Financial Adviser appointed under sub-section (1) shall be the Chief Accounts Officer of the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(4) The terms and conditions of service of the Chief Engineer of the Board, and of the Financial`
  line `Adviser, and the Secretary, to the Board shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12510)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Other officers and employees of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12510&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the rules, the Board may appoint`
  line `such officers and employees as it may deem necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall, as far as practicable, utilise the services of the officers and employees`
  line `offered by the Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh in such a manner that equal`
  line `representation is given to the two States.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of the officers and employees of the Board shall be such as`
  line `may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12511)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Advisory Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12511&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the rules, the Board may from time to time, constitute one or`
  line `more Advisory Committees to assist the Board and the Executive Committee in the efficient discharge of`
  line `their functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12512)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Functions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-12-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12512&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the other provisions of this Act and the rules, the Board`
  line `may, if satisfied that the Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh have complied with or`
  line `arranged to comply with the conditions specified in section 11,--`
  line
  line `(a) carry out surveys and investigations in the Betwa Inter-State river valley and prepare a`
  line `comprehensive project report for the construction of Rajghat Dam and appurtenant works ^1[and for`
  line `the generation of power at Rajghat Dam, including the construction of a power house (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the Rajghat Power House) near the dam and appurtenant works] and finalise the same`
  line `after consulting the Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh and taking into account the`
  line `suggestions if any made by those Governments;`
  line
  line `(b) prepare detailed reports and estimates in respect of the Project and allocate the cost among the`
  line `Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(c) draw up standards and specifications for implementation of the project and for the`
  line `maintenance thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) construct the Rajghat Dam ^1[and the Rajghat Power House] and the common carrier from the`
  line `dam to irrigate areas in Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(e) lay down rules of operation and management of Rajghat Dam;`
  line
  line `(f) perform any other function which is supplemental, incidental, or consequential to all or any of`
  line `the functions specified in clauses (a) to (e).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12513)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Conditions subject to which the Board may exercise its functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1977, s. 5, for "Rajghat Dam including appurtenantworks" (w.e.f. 26-12-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12513&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The exercise by the`
  line `Board of the functions specified in section 10 shall be subject to the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) that the Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh shall at all times make, to the`
  line `satisfaction of the Board, suitable provisions as to the moneys, land facilities and electrical power for`
  line `construction and all other things required by the Board;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the liability for the entire expenditure on the ^1[Rajghat Dam and Rajghat Power House`
  line `including appurtenant works and on the generation of power at Rajghat Dam] and all other`
  line `expenditure incurred by the Board in the discharge of its functions shall be shared by the`
  line `Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh in such proportion as may be specified by the`
  line `Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may specify different proportions for different works or matters having`
  line `regard to the benefits which may accrue to the States and other relevant factors;`
  line
  line `(iii) that the Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh shall extend full co-operation to`
  line `the Board and shall in particular make available to the Board the land and electric power required by`
  line `it for construction purposes as expeditiously as possible.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of clause (ii) of sub-section (1), the expenditure on the Rajghat Dam shall`
  line `include the expenditure incurred by the Government of Uttar Pradesh on the Rajghat Dam Project before`
  line `the establishment of the Board and the Board shall determine the amount of expenditure so incurred by`
  line `the Government of Uttar Pradesh and the extent to which it shall be reimbursed by the Government of`
  line `Madhya Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12514)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Powers of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12514&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules, the Board shall`
  line `have the power to do anything which may be necessary or expedient for the purpose of carrying out its`
  line `functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, such power shall include the`
  line powers--
  line
  line `(a) to acquire, hold and dispose of such properties both movable and immovable as the Board`
  line `deems necessary;`
  line
  line `(b) to publish statistics or other information relating to the various aspects of flood control and`
  line `drainage in the Betwa River Valley ^1[, the regulation of ^2[Rani Laxmibai Sagar] and the generation of`
  line `power at Rajghat Dam];`
  line
  line `(c) to require the Governments of Uttar Pradesh and Madhya Pradesh to furnish such information`
  line `as the Board may require in the discharge of its functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "and the regulation of Rajghat Reservoir" (w.e.f. 26-12-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 1993, s. 3, for "Rajghat Reservoir" (w.e.f. 27-8-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12515)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Betwa River Board Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1977, s. 7, for "Rajghat Dam and appurtenant works" (w.e.f. 26-12-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12515&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called the Betwa River`
  line `Board Fund and there shall be credited thereto the sums paid to the Board by the Governments of Madhya`
  line `Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh and all other sums received by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) for meeting the salaries, allowances and other remuneration of the officers and other`
  line `employees of the Board and other administrative expenses of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) for meeting the expenditure on surveys and investigations undertaken by the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) for meeting the cost of construction of the ^1[Rajghat Dam, the Rajghat Power House and`
  line `appurtenant works];`
  line
  line `(d) for meeting the other expenses of the Board in the discharge of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12516)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12516&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare in such form and at such time each year as may be prescribed`
  line `its budget for the next financial year showing the estimated expenditure, the amount of expenditure which`
  line `the State Governments of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh have undertaken to provide for and forward`
  line `the same to the Central Government and the said State Governments.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12517)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12517&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall prepare in such form and at such time each year as may be`
  line `prescribed its annual report giving a full account of its activities during the previous year and forward`
  line `copies thereof to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall forward copies of its annual reports to the Governments of Madhya Pradesh and`
  line `Uttar Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12518)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12518&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The accounts of the Board shall be maintained and audited in such manner`
  line `as may, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12519)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12519&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `In the discharge of its functions, the Board shall be`
  line `guided by such directions and instructions on questions of policy as may be given to it by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12520)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Disputes between the Board and the State Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12520&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `If any dispute arises between the`
  line `Board and the Government of Madhya Pradesh or Uttar Pradesh or both regarding any matter covered by`
  line `this Act or touching or arising out of it, it shall be referred to the Central Government and the decision of`
  line `the Central Government shall be final and binding on the Board and the said Governments.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12521)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to enter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12521&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made in this behalf, any officer of the Board generally or`
  line `specially authorised by the Board in this behalf may, at all reasonable times, enter upon any land or`
  line `premises and there do such things as may be reasonably necessary for the purpose of lawfully carrying`
  line `out any works or of making any surveys, examination or investigation, preliminary or incidental to the`
  line `exercise of any power or the performance of any function by the Board under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall enter into any building or upon any enclosed court or garden attached to`
  line `a dwelling house, unless with the consent of the occupier thereof, without previously giving such occupier`
  line `at least seven days' notice in writing of his intention to do so.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (12522)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Members, officers and employees of the Board to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12522&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `All members of the`
  line `Board and the Executive Committee and all officers and employees of the Board shall be deemed, when`
  line `acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act to be public servants within`
  line `the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (12523)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12523&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or the Government of Madhya Pradesh or Uttar Pradesh or any`
  line `member of the Board or the Executive Committee or any officer or employee of the Board for anything`
  line `which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules or regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against the Board for any damage caused or likely to`
  line `be caused by anything in good faith done or purported to be done under this Act or the rules or`
  line `regulations and, in particular, it shall not be the responsibility of the Board to provide for relief measures`
  line `necessitated by floods or by breaches and failure of works.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (12524)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12524&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the composition of, and the procedure to be followed, by the Executive Committee and all`
  line `other matters relating to the Executive Committee, under sub-sections (2) and (5) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers and duties which may be exercised or discharged by the Chief Engineer of the`
  line `Board, under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions of service of the Chief Engineer of, and the Financial Adviser and`
  line `the Secretary to, the Board, under sub-section (4) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) appointment of officers and employees of the Board, under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which and the time at which the budget and annual report of the Board shall be`
  line `prepared, under section 14, and sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which the accounts of the Board shall be maintained and audited, under section`
  line 16;
  line
  line `(g) the form and manner in which disputes may be referred under section 18 to the Central`
  line `Government and the procedure to be followed by the Central Government for the settlement of such`
  line disputes.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (12525)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12525&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations not inconsistent with this Act and`
  line `the rules, for enabling it to discharge its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may provide for all`
  line `or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which and the purposes for which the Board may associate with itself any`
  line `persons, under sub-section (5) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers which may be exercised and the duties which may be discharged by the Chief`
  line `Engineer of the Board, under sub-section (2) (b) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions of service of the officers (other than the Chief Engineer of the Board,`
  line `Financial Adviser and Secretary to the Board) and other employees of the Board, under sub-section`
  line `(2) of section 8.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (12526)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578&sectionId=12526&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00001_197663_1517807318578
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation, as`
  line `the case may be, or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation, as the case may be, should not be made,`
  line `the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `बेतवा नदी बोर्ड अधिनियम, 1976`
  sourceUrl `https://www.indiacode.nic.in/bitstream/123456789/1479/4/H1976-63.pdf`
  sourceKind pdf
  fetchedAt `2026-05-10T11:27:05.822Z`
